# Action Source

## Parser registration order

In `src/parsers/registry.ts`, order is TRX → NUnit → xUnit → JUnit. More specific parsers must come before generic ones for XML auto-detection.

## Adding a parser

1. Implement `TestResultParser` from `src/parsers/types.ts`.
2. Map to normalized `TestCase` in `src/model/test-case.ts`.
3. Register in `src/parsers/registry.ts`.
4. Add fixture in `test/fixtures/` and tests in `test/parsers/`.

## Build output

- `dist/index.js` is committed — run `npm run build` after source changes (esbuild bundle).
- `lib/` is generated by `tsc` and gitignored — never edit.
- Generator assets are copied to `dist/assets/` via `scripts/copy-assets.js`.

## Config

`src/config.ts` reads all inputs from `action.yml`. When adding inputs, update `action.yml`, `config.ts`, and `docs/docs/reference/configuration.md`.
